phone  address  age  more search free uncover potential relatives location history photos  videos email address next search the web  aol inc all rights reservedprivacy   terms of use   preferences   contact us   powered by bing™ wowcom  part of the aol search network vernon hill  wikipedia vernon hill from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search for other people named vernon hill see vernon hill disambiguation metro bank borehamwood vernon w hill ii born august   is an american businessman the founder and chairman of metro bank a uk retail bank with  stores and assets of £b b he is also the founder former chairman president and ceo of commerce bancorp of cherry hill new jersey and chairman of fetch inc aka pet plan north america contents  early career  commerce bancorp  petplan  metro bank  book  other investments  business philosophy  personal life  references early careeredit although known for banking hill’s business outlook has been informed by early encounters with retailing while taking morning classes at wharton hill worked afternoons at a south jersey bank owned by a local car retailer where hill observed the car dealer applying retail principles to banking operations such as late opening hours the job also brought hill into contact with other local retailers including mcdonalds after graduation hill founded a real estate firm to find and develop sites for mcdonalds a task which required hill to drive mcdonalds entrepreneur ray kroc on scouting trips hill claims his experience with mcdonald’s taught him the importance of standardised presentation and scale economies in retailing philadelphia magazine reports that hill’s experience with mcdonald’s led directly to the creation of commerce bank referring to the creation of commerce morton kerr chairman of the board of markeimchalmers inc a south jersey real estate firm and one of the original commerce board members observed “a lot of us knew vernon from being involved in real estate at that time…he was a yearold kid who called about  of us to a meeting in his office ill never forget it he said were going to start a bank and he said wed each have to put up between  and  this was who had that kind of money but hed arranged for all of us to borrow it if you could put up  he got us loans for  only seven of us didnt get up and walk out but we still thought he was crazy” the deal resulted in commerce opening its first branch in marlton new jersey in  commerce bancorpedit commerce bank was notable for its rapid expansion from one branch in  to  branches in  and a deposit base that grew by an average of  per year between  and  against an industry average of  in  according to forbes magazine commerce produced a  annual shareholder return compounded for  years commerce bank’s economic model rested on the idea that the fixed costs of a bank branch are largely independent of volume and so profitability lay in maximizing the number of deposits and accounts per branch additionally hill believed that the industrys reliance on internet banking had led to disinvestment in bank branches to the detriment of consumers who prioritised inperson service “other banks decided to push consumers out of the branch because it is the highcost delivery channel they wanted to push them online we totally reject that you can’t name me one retailer in this country that has pushed people where they don’t want to go and succeeded…we have some branches that get  customer visits a month the average branch gets  an average mcdonald’s gets  per month” hill’s motto for commerce was “america’s most convenient bank” commerce tactics were oriented to drive volume differentiation and customer advocacy including longer opening hours including evenings and weekends opening ten minutes earlier and later than advertised hours removing glass from teller booths for a more open customer experience petfriendly policies giveaways such as lollipops and dog biscuits free use of coincounting machines handing out pens in response to rival banks’ practice of chaining pens to desks “kill the stupid rule” program whereby employees who suggested an alternative to a stupid rule were paid  commerce bank staff were awarded  if a nearby rival bank closed its branches hundreds of mystery shoppers made tens of thousands of store visits annually and salary increases were based on mystery shopping scores topperforming managers were given sports cars on june   hill resigned as chairman and ceo of commerce bancorp after the office of the comptroller of the currency the federal reserve bank of philadelphia and the board of directors of commerce bancorp established governance to stop doing business with firms under the control of hill’s family notable business dealings with insiders included property leases with entities in which hill was a partner and the purchase of services from an architectural design business run by his wife shirley no charges were brought on october   commerce bancorp announced that it would be merging with td bank financial group the canadianbased torontodominion bank would acquire commerce for  billion us dollars in cash and stock at  per share of cbh stock a purchase multiple of x some industry commentators held that hills departure and a strong canadian dollar had made a takeover inevitable petplanedit hill is chairman of fetch inc aka petplan north america a pet health insurance company founded by chris and natasha ashton it holds the us and canadian franchise from petplan of britain the worlds biggest provider of policies for companion animals hill invested in the company in april  believing pet health to be a growth market in the usa speaking to fortune magazine in  hill said people used to put down their pets when they got sick now theyre members of the family people will want to save them with kidney transplants and hip replacements this business will be hugecitation needed metro bankedit metro bank uk was launched in london july  with hill as cofounder and vicechairman press commentary at the time centred on metro being the first highstreet bank to open in the united kingdom for more than  years and upon hills belief that the competitive landscape of british banking amounted to a commercial opportunity to lead on service rather than price in   of the uk market for current accounts was held by the “big five” banking institutions hsbc barclays royal bank of scotland santander and lloyds in  an official report from the office of fair trading concluded that uk banking was subject to weak competitive pressures and profitmaximising strategies forbes magazine described metro at launch as aiming to disrupt a storied industry dominated by a handful of established players in a bbc news interview thomson commented that the cost–driven model of traditional british banks required them to discourage customers from visiting branches whereas metro bank’s model actively sought to attract customers into branches using tactics such as longer opening hours and petfriendly policies the pair spent a further two years securing a £m launch investment including funds from new york real estate developer richard lefrak property investors the reuben brothers and fidelity the fund management company metro launched with plans to open  branches in london by  twelve branches were opened by december  in june  the company announced the completion of a £m round of capitalraising to open further branches in london including funds from moore capital and billionaire investor steve cohen noted investor wilbur ross commented that the question is whether hill’s promotional flair and service concept will produce enough customers to offset the extra operational cost of providing the extra space hill who previously served as metros vice chairman replaced his cofounder anthony thomson as chairman in january  as of september  metro had  accounts and was opening a new branch every month with a goal of opening  by the close of the year in may metro opened a drivethrough bank in slough the second in the uk after natwest in toxteth liverpool which opened in  but has since closed in  in april  hill was also awarded the institute of economic affairs free enterprise award whose previous winners include margaret thatcher and sir richard branson for his work at metro the iea noted hill has identified a clear opportunity and entered the uk banking scene at a time when the sector has been under constant fire and showed incredible perseverance and imagination while iea director general mark littlewood praised metro bank as a shining example of innovation improving peoples live its refreshing to see more competition and choice in the banking sector on our high streets in august  tom brown of bankstockscom wrote so vernon hill has not once but twice and in two different markets built growth machines in the supposedly mature and sleepy banking business that has to make him the world’s greatest growthoriented banker probably of all time in the same month hill received the  stevie award for international chairman of the year bookedit hill is the author of fans not customers how to create growth companies in a no growth world which was released by profile books in october  it argues that it is better to have fans rather than customers and urges businesses to compete on service rather than price the financial times reviewed hills writing style as refreshingly to the point and said that for those looking for an alternate way of approaching service the book will prove rich pickings other investmentsedit hill is a partner with steve lewis in us restaurants inc which operates  burger king restaurants in metropolitan philadelphia hills first business was site development inc a real estate development firm which has developed over  shopping centres and retail developments in america in  hill along with partners john silvestri and steve lewis founded and developed galloway national golf club near atlantic city new jersey the course was designed by tom fazio and is ranked by golfdigestcom as being among the top  courses in americacitation needed business philosophyedit fortune magazine describes hill as a “flamboyant traditionstomping american billionaire…the pt barnum of banking” hill has often advocated a business development strategy based on organic growth rather than acquisition and by generating customer loyalty through service rather than price speaking to a  house of commons treasury select committee on competition and choice in the banking sector hill said “my opinion is that great retailers never grow by acquisition…if you see yourself as a retailer delivering an unusual service acquisitions are the easiest way to kill your model…organic growth is slower but you get what you want at the end you get a group of people running your model not somebody else’s model…” hill is a critic of the shadow banking system believing it to largely responsible for the  global financial crisis “we have two american banking systems we have the normal banking system with  banks serving consumers and businesses throughout america then we developed a shadow banking system…the money market funds the investment banks the credit default swaps the current crisis is really a crisis of this shadow banking system…i think when banks are making a loan to say a restaurant the overwhelming majority of banks aren’t playing games as long as the guy’s paying it’s a loan that pays back over time then we moved into all this exotic stuff — credit default swaps cdos believe me no one at goldman sachs understands what they have on their books because these kids are sitting at their computers dreaming this stuff up…” hill is often quoted as viewing his banks to be in the retail business rather than the banking business “you dont have to think about what time a home depot a mcdonalds or a starbucks is open” hill says “theyre open you just go my theory was if you advertise that your bank is open on sunday the consumer will automatically believe youre open all the time that message is more important than the savings in its   club forbes magazine lists hill as one of seven ceos along with warren buffett and larry ellison of publicly traded companies with tenures of over  years to deliver an annual shareholder return in excess of  commerce produced a  annual compounded shareholder return over that time personal lifeedit hill is the son of a virginia real estate brokerage owner and the eldest of six children he graduated from wharton school of the university of pennsylvania in philadelphia in  earning a bs in economics with a concentration in finance hills  ft²  m² home villa collina is located in moorestown township new jersey the home features an orangery hill has been married for  years to shirley hill who is the founder of interarch the architectural and branding firm responsible for the branding for commerce bank and metro bank the couple have four children and sir duffield their yorkshire terrier the hill family foundation supports various charitable organisations in both the us and britain it is one of the largestcitation needed supporters of veterinary causes including a  million gift for the vernon and shirley hill pavilion at the school of veterinary medicine at the university of pennsylvania vernons alma mater the penn world veterinary award the uk kennel club achievement award referencesedit  a b vernon the barbarian philadelphia magazine august  retrieved  august    tully shawn vernon hill is the best damn banker alive just ask him fortune magazine cnn retrieved  october  i was fascinated at how mcdonalds created the same look and same experience in every location says hill i also learned that costs are relatively fixed so its all about volume   a b murphy andrea  may  chiefs in the  club forbes retrieved  august  its no easy feat to make it onto our  list a chief executive has to have held the top job for at least  yearsat a company with publicly traded shares for at least  yearsand have presided over at least a  annual return in share price during his or her tenure   frei frances commerce bank  harvard business review p  retrieved  august    wharton alumni magazine  influential people and ideas vernon w hill ii wharton   commerce minus larger than life entrepreneur financial post retrieved  august    grant tavia  october  how vernon w hill built  and lost  a banking empire globe and mail archived from the original on  june  retrieved  december    mulvihill geoff  october  after commerce bancorps founder is ousted td bank pounces with  billion acquisition san diego uniontribune retrieved  december    benner katie october   a health care plan for fido fortune magazine retrieved  august    moore elaine challengers needed’ for big five banks financial times retrieved  august    personal current account market not working well for consumers says oft office of fair trading july  retrieved  august    olson parmy  march  vernon hill beefs up whopper banking in london forbescom retrieved  august  having opened his first british store last july in holborn london hill has come to britain with a similar mandate to offer customers good service over good interest rates and promising no stupid bank rules   metro bank opens doors in uk bbccouk  july  retrieved  august  metro bank hopes to gain customers dissatisfied with their existing banks   bates victoria  november  metro bank taps investors for £m to speed up expansion city am retrieved  august    baird roger  august  the latenight bank manager is planning a high street revolution city am retrieved  august  metro bank plans to open another three branches in earl’s court fulham broadway and borehamwood by the end of the year and eight more next year the aim is to have  branches in greater london by  it plans to open  current accounts in its first year   dunne john metro bank eyes expansion after raising £m city am retrieved  august    edwards peter  june  float looms for growing metro city am retrieved  august    metro bank opens doors in uk wilbur ross on vernon hills new uk bank and his own   abbas mohammed  january  uks metro bank appoints vernon hill as new chair reuters retrieved  september    armitstead louise  april  monday interview allamerican shakeup comes to uk banking telegraph london retrieved  september    gore alex  may  would you like fries with that £ britains firstever drivethru bank was natwest in toxteth liverpool opening in  opens to ease motorists through transactions daily mail london retrieved  september    a b iea awards free enterprise award to vernon hill institute of economic affairs retrieved  september    bankstockscom august    the stevie awards august  retrieved  september    fans not customers how to create growth companies in a no growth world paperback amazoncouk retrieved  september    timmins matt fans not customers by vernon hill financial times retrieved  september    a little bit about us us restaurants archived from the original on june   retrieved  september    executive team retrieved  august    tully shawn  vernon hill is the best damn banker alive just ask him forbes   treasury committee competition and choice in the banking sector hansard retrieved  august    this too shall pass philadelphia magazine retrieved  august    smith eileen and walsh jim hills climb took bank to heights of industry asbury park press june   accessed july   hill and his wife shirley built villa collina literally hill house a squarefoot  m tuscanstyle mansion in moorestown that is the biggest private residence in the state  hyman vicki  july  banker vernon hill owner of njs largest mansion selling shore home m nj advance media retrieved  july    distefano joseph n commerce bancorp chairman gives  million to veterinary school the philadelphia inquirer october   accessed october   penn said that the hills have given  million to the vet school toward a  million classroom and office center that penn will call the vernon and shirley hill pavilion  penn world veterinary awards retrieved  september    the kennel club the kennel club retrieved  september   retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlevernonhilloldid categories  birthsliving peoplecommerce bancorpwharton school of the university of pennsylvania alumnipeople from moorestown new jerseyamerican bankersamerican chief executives of financial services companiesbank presidents and chief executive officershidden categories all articles with unsourced statementsarticles with unsourced statements from december articles with unsourced statements from january articles with unsourced statements from june  navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesupload filespecial pagespermanent linkpage informationwikidata itemcite this page printexport create a bookdownload as pdfprintable version in other projects wikimedia commons languages add links this page was last edited on  july  at  text is available under the creative commons attributionsharealike license additional terms may apply by using this site you agree to the terms of use and privacy policy wikipedia® is a registered trademark of the wikimedia foundation inc a nonprofit organization privacy policy about wikipedia disclaimers contact wikipedia developers cookie statement mobile view vernon hill  wikipedia vernon hill from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search for other people named vernon hill see vernon hill disambiguation metro bank borehamwood vernon w hill ii born august   is an american businessman the founder and chairman of metro bank a uk retail bank with  stores and assets of £b b he is also the founder former chairman president and ceo of commerce bancorp of cherry 